dismissalComment.html: oh well held, Randiv! Another slow loopy delivery on leg stump and Gambhir looks to again turn it away, this time there is some turn and he gets a leading edge that pops up and starts to die but Randiv scampers forward and dives forward to pluck it an inch off the grass ... Gambhir is not convinced and waits for replays which show the bowler did indeed take a really good catch in his followthrough

headshotImage.longCaption: Chanaka Welegedara player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: full down the pads, misses everything and India lead the series!

commentPostTextItems.html: Good win this, one set in motion in the field when Sri Lanka lost nine wickets for 74 runs and slumped to 239. Nehra, Jadeja, Harbhajan and Ishant did the hard work then, and after a rousing 44 from Sehwag, Tendulkar patiently made an unbeaten 96. The fans wanted a century from him but he didn't manage one. Personal records should not matter, because the real victory is that India have taken a lead in the series.
Stick around for the post-match presentation.
Sangakkara says the bowlers tried hard but that Sri Lanka did not have enough runs after that mad collapse. Wants to keep fighting and enjoying. Believes Sri Lanka can come back into the series.
Sehwag says he was praying Sri Lanka did not cross 400. Credits the spinners for doing well. But has to name himself for taking a wicket. Good fun. Thanks Tendulkar for helping India win easily.

Jadeja is the Man of the Match for his four wickets. A crucial performance it was indeed. Yes sir, he says when asked by Ravi Shastri if he enjoyed himself. Classic Now he gets down to talking in Hindi. Says he liked the way he bowled, wanted to bowl slower, vary his pace. Adds that he is confident of keeping his place in the team. Thank you, sir, he signs off with. Foh fweet, as Charlie would say.
So that brings us to the end of the third ODI. Do join us for game four on December 24. Okay bye!

commentTextItems.html: loud shot as Karthik gets an inside edge, no chance
goes full outside off, he stands there and opens the face, steering the ball out to third man

commentPreTextItems.html: Seven to win. Two fours for Tendulkar?

commentTextItems.html: well there's one of them, as he again walks across early and clips an inside edge off a full ball down the pads, beating a diving Sangakkara
pitches outside leg and he turns it to midwicket

commentTextItems.html: maximum! Dances out, collects on the full, and dumps it over long-on
pushes it through just outside the line of impact, Karthik stabs at it and gets an inside edge
slower ball, spins in, he defends and the ball gets tangled in his pad
dances out and hits it on the bounce to the man down at long-on

commentPreTextItems.html: Right, so Tendulkar needs ten, India need 14.

commentTextItems.html: tossed up, Tendulkar sweeps from outside off stump with the turn, misses and survives marginally because he was hit slightly outside the line
swing there, another good yorker, Karthik clears his front leg and digs it out

commentTextItems.html: short of a length and Karthik stands tall to keep the ball at his feet

dangerous, walks right across his stumps and tries to paddle it, the ball is not as full and strikes him on the back leg, a very confident appeal but enough doubt in the mind because he was on the hop
good placement from Tendulkar, who premeditates the full ball and walks across to flick it wide of deep fine leg for four
good ball, aims for the yorker, gets some swing, Tendulkar walks across and gets an inside edge
full outside leg stump, flicks the pads and runs to deep fine leg

commentPreTextItems.html: Mid-on goes back for the last ball ...

commentTextItems.html: sweeps from outside off stump with the turn and hits it hard, getting Kulasekara running across from fine leg, and that is the 50-run stand

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Karthik b Nehra 41 (18b 10x4 0x6 37m) SR: 227.77

dismissalComment.html: whew, relief for India and the crowd explodes! Nehra drags it short, Dilshan harries out and goes for a pull, its too short and he gets a top edge off the shoulder of the bat and Karthik runs back to hold it, had he dropped that ... ummm ....

headshotImage.caption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara st Karthik b Sehwag 46 (41b 3x4 1x6 62m) SR: 112.19

dismissalComment.html: stumped, on the second attempt! Sangakkara dances down the track and looks to whip it against the turn, he's beaten in the air and the ball breaks away off the track, Karthik fumbles the collection but regroups to break the stumps on the second attempt, take that blooming baseball grill off, man

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga b Jadeja 73 (81b 6x4 1x6 110m) SR: 90.12

dismissalComment.html: bowled em! Well done Jadeja, tosses it up on a length outside off stump, Tharanga drives at the ball against the spin with a massive gap between bat and pad, the ball pitches and turns in a long, long way and hits off stump

headshotImage.caption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Raina b Harbhajan Singh 2 (12b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: short ball gets a wicket! Harbhajan drags it down, Jayawardene goes for a pull but hits it straight to a leaping Raina at midwicket, and he cannot believe it

headshotImage.caption: Chamara Kapugedera player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Kapugedera player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Chamara Kapugedera player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Kapugedera player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamara Kapugedera b Jadeja 15 (28b 0x4 0x6 32m) SR: 53.57

dismissalComment.html: dragged on! A nothing dismissal, as Kapudegera goes back and chases the ball away from his body and chops it back onto his sticks

dismissalText.commentary: Thilina Kandamby b Sharma 22 (29b 3x4 0x6 44m) SR: 75.86

dismissalComment.html: bowled em! Ishant continues his very good spell by keeping it full and straight to Kandamby who presses forward on the defensive and gets an inside edge as the ball straightens a wee bit after pitching, the top off off stump goes back and Ishant is absolutely loving it

headshotImage.caption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Suraj Randiv c Karthik b Sharma 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: edged and gone! Two in two for Ishant and its because of that fuller length and the bit of movement it produces! This one is again pitched up to Randiv who pushes at it off the front foot and gets the faintest of edges through to Karthik

dismissalText.commentary: Nuwan Kulasekara lbw b Jadeja 10 (14b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: that is plumb! Jadeja continues to plug away from around the stumps, pushing in an arm ball that slides on and hits Kulasekara in front of middle and leg as the bat comes down late on the attempted defensive shot back down the track

dismissalText.commentary: Ajantha Mendis b Jadeja 6 (14b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: lovely way to end his spell! Slows the pace, tosses it up just outside the line, gets a little bit of turn back in but its enough to slide past the bat and hit off stump

headshotImage.longCaption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lasith Malinga b Nehra 13 (24b 1x4 1x6 32m) SR: 54.16

dismissalComment.html: that is that! Nehra goes full just outside off stump, Malinga stands there and swings and inside-edges onto the base of his stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Gautam Gambhir c & b Randiv 32 (52b 3x4 0x6 64m) SR: 61.53

dismissalComment.html: oh well held, Randiv! Another slow loopy delivery on leg stump and Gambhir looks to again turn it away, this time there is some turn and he gets a leading edge that pops up and starts to die but Randiv scampers forward and dives forward to pluck it an inch off the grass ... Gambhir is not convinced and waits for replays which show the bowler did indeed take a really good catch in his followthrough

headshotImage.caption: Chanaka Welegedara player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chanaka Welegedara player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Yuvraj Singh c Sangakkara b Welegedara 23 (40b 3x4 0x6 46m) SR: 57.5

dismissalComment.html: nicked and gone! Welegedara smartly follows the bouncer with a fuller and wider ball which lures Yuvraj into a terrible drive away from the body, the lack of coordination does for him and Sangakkara takes the outside edge
